3#ifndef __NVBIOS_PLL_H__
4#define __NVBIOS_PLL_H__
5/*XXX: kill me */
6struct nvkm_pll_vals {
7 union {
8 struct {
9#ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN
10 uint8_t N1, M1, N2, M2;
11#else
12 uint8_t M1, N1, M2, N2;
13#endif
14 };
15 struct {
16 uint16_t NM1, NM2;
17 } __attribute__((packed));
18 };
19 int log2P;
20
21 int refclk;
22};
23
24/* these match types in pll limits table version 0x40,
25 * nvkm uses them on all chipsets internally where a
26 * specific pll needs to be referenced, but the exact
27 * register isn't known.
28 */
29enum nvbios_pll_type {
30 PLL_CORE = 0x01,
31 PLL_SHADER = 0x02,
32 PLL_UNK03 = 0x03,
33 PLL_MEMORY = 0x04,
34 PLL_VDEC = 0x05,
35 PLL_UNK40 = 0x40,
36 PLL_UNK41 = 0x41,
37 PLL_UNK42 = 0x42,
38 PLL_VPLL0 = 0x80,
39 PLL_VPLL1 = 0x81,
40 PLL_VPLL2 = 0x82,
41 PLL_VPLL3 = 0x83,
42 PLL_MAX = 0xff
43};
44
45struct nvbios_pll {
46 enum nvbios_pll_type type;
47 u32 reg;
48 u32 refclk;
49
50 u8 min_p;
51 u8 max_p;
52 u8 bias_p;
53
54 /*
55 * for most pre nv50 cards setting a log2P of 7 (the common max_log2p
56 * value) is no different to 6 (at least for vplls) so allowing the MNP
57 * calc to use 7 causes the generated clock to be out by a factor of 2.
58 * however, max_log2p cannot be fixed-up during parsing as the
59 * unmodified max_log2p value is still needed for setting mplls, hence
60 * an additional max_usable_log2p member
61 */
62 u8 max_p_usable;
63
64 struct {
65 u32 min_freq;
66 u32 max_freq;
67 u32 min_inputfreq;
68 u32 max_inputfreq;
69 u8 min_m;
70 u8 max_m;
71 u8 min_n;
72 u8 max_n;
73 } vco1, vco2;
74};
75
76int nvbios_pll_parse(struct nvkm_bios *, u32 type, struct nvbios_pll *);
77#endif
